1. Creational Patterns

These deal with object creation.

Singleton Pattern
Definition

Ensures that only one object of a class is created.

Real-Life Example
Printer Spooler
Logger
Database Connection
Configuration Manager
Implementation
class Singleton {

    private static Singleton instance;

    private Singleton() {
    }

    public static Singleton getInstance() {

        if(instance == null)
            instance = new Singleton();

        return instance;
    }
}

Usage:

Singleton obj1 = Singleton.getInstance();
Singleton obj2 = Singleton.getInstance();

System.out.println(obj1 == obj2);

Output:

true
Advantages

✔ Saves memory

✔ Global access point

✔ Prevents multiple objects

Factory Pattern 
Definition

Creates objects without exposing creation logic.

Without Factory
Car c = new Car();
Bike b = new Bike();
Truck t = new Truck();

Client needs to know every class.

With Factory

Step 1

interface Vehicle{
    void drive();
}

Step 2

class Car implements Vehicle{

    public void drive(){
        System.out.println("Car");
    }
}

class Bike implements Vehicle{

    public void drive(){
        System.out.println("Bike");
    }
}

Step 3

class VehicleFactory{

    public Vehicle getVehicle(String type){

        if(type.equals("car"))
            return new Car();

        else
            return new Bike();
    }
}

Usage:

VehicleFactory vf = new VehicleFactory();

Vehicle v = vf.getVehicle("car");

v.drive();
Real-Life Example

Restaurant Menu

Customer orders food.

Kitchen decides how to prepare it.

Customer doesn't know the creation process.

Advantages

 Loose coupling

 Easy extension

 Supports OCP

 Builder Pattern 
Definition

Used when objects have many parameters.

Without Builder:

Student s =
new Student("Rahul",22,"Delhi","B.Tech",987654321);

Confusing constructor.

With Builder:

Student s = new StudentBuilder()
            .setName("Rahul")
            .setAge(22)
            .setCity("Delhi")
            .build();
Real-Life Example

Ordering Pizza

Choose:

Size
Cheese
Toppings

Then build pizza.

Advantages

 Readable code

 Immutable objects

 Flexible construction



